-- 0254 — per-line "แก้ยอดเรียกเก็บ" OVERRIDE flag on ใบวางบิล line items.
--
-- WHY (MONEY · bill live-view→freeze 2026-07-13 · money-review blocker):
--   The shared resolver (lib/billing/resolve-bill-amounts.ts) reflows every PRICED
--   line from the LIVE forwarder GROSS while a bill is amount-live (issued · no slip ·
--   no active receipt), and the commit freeze then writes that reflowed value. A line
--   the admin MANUALLY OVERRODE (typed a figure ≠ the auto gross in the /add form's
--   "แก้ยอดเรียกเก็บ" field) has NO live forwarder source, so the reflow/refreeze
--   silently reverts it to gross → the customer is billed/paid the wrong amount
--   (e.g. admin typed ฿500 on a ฿800-gross row → paper/QR/receipt show ฿800). The
--   resolver cannot tell a stored override from a stored auto-gross without a
--   persisted signal — this boolean IS that signal. loader/list/freeze read it and
--   route flagged lines through the resolver's `overrides` map (override wins · never
--   reflows), so bill == receipt == list == /b/[token] QR by construction (guardrail b),
--   and a paid amount never silently changes (guardrail c).
--
-- BACKFILL-SAFE: DEFAULT false. Existing lines are treated as auto — legacy
--   zeroTransport (gross≤0) overrides stay protected by the resolver's gross<=0
--   preservation floor; legacy PRICED-override rows on a still-issued bill remain the
--   pre-existing ambiguity (unflaggable without the create-time gross) until re-issued.
--   Committed/paid legacy bills are already safe (frozen · reflow off).
--
-- ⚠️ APPLY TO prod + dev BEFORE the reading code merges (mig-ledger convention · the
--    create INSERT + the 3 read SELECTs reference this column). Idempotent.
